rtainties) and they show a significant relative\nproper motion. The distances are shown to be robust. HD 193 322 Aa,Ab follows\nan eccentric (e = 0.58+0.03-0.04) orbit with a period of 44+-1 a and the three\nstars it contains have a total mass of 76.1+9.9-7.4 M_Sol. The orbit of 15 Mon\nAa,Ab is even more eccentric (e = 0.770+0.023-0.030), with a period of 108+-12\na and a total mass of 45.1+3.6-3.3 M_Sol for its two stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 6 Aug 2019 09:45:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-02"}
